The paper focuses on the evolutionary synthesis of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the genetic encoding scheme used to mimic heredity, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the synthesized networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the tailored network architectures for GPU-accelerated machine learning applications, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
